{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01R2v9hoaHd7wocHKuiuSCHd","type":"tool_result","content":"453\t**And** codex driver warns and ignores unsupported plugins\n454\t**And** plugin configuration does not require modifying the plugins themselves (NFR12)\n455\t\n456\t### Story 6.2: Cost Tracking Per Driver\n457\t\n458\tAs a user,\n459\tI want to see accumulated cost per driver across a workflow run,\n460\tSo that I can compare framework costs and optimize.\n461\t\n462\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n463\t\n464\t**Given** a multi-driver workflow run\n465\t**When** tasks complete on different drivers\n466\t**Then** the engine accumulates cost per driver\n467\t**And** total cost per driver is displayed in the TUI\n468\t**And** drivers that don't report cost show `null` (not $0)\n469\t\n470\t### Story 6.3: Driver Capability Matrix & Routing Hints\n471\t\n472\tAs a user,\n473\tI want the system to warn me about capability conflicts and suggest cheaper alternatives,\n474\tSo that I avoid misconfigurations and optimize costs.\n475\t\n476\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n477\t\n478\t**Given** driver capabilities defined in `factory.ts`\n479\t**When** a workflow starts\n480\t**Then** the engine warns if a task's requirements conflict with the driver's capabilities\n481\t**And** `codeharness drivers` CLI command outputs capabilities as structured JSON\n482\t**And** when a task's driver costs >2x the cheapest capable alternative, an advisory message is displayed\n483\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01FRDwwzfG8xnd7jPHer3uP2","session_id":"a0646c12-93c6-41a0-9c7a-50683cae7716","uuid":"31a9928b-ee54-4482-b188-e1b22f763f59","timestamp":"2026-04-03T12:48:32.805Z"}
