{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014N4Uyv2DTmpZDToNJAsYpe","type":"tool_result","content":"46-### Cross-Cutting Concerns Identified\n47-\n48-1. **Driver lifecycle management** — Spawning, monitoring, timeout, termination, crash recovery applies to all drivers. Must be uniform regardless of whether the driver is in-process (Agent SDK) or CLI-wrapped (Codex, OpenCode).\n49:2. **Stream event normalization** — Every driver must produce `StreamEvent` objects. The TUI, cost tracker, and workflow engine all consume these. A driver that drops events or misparses output breaks everything downstream.\n50-3. **Output contract integrity** — Cross-framework task execution depends on output contracts being complete, correctly serialized, and crash-safe. A corrupted contract means the next task gets garbage context.\n51-4. **Model resolution cascade** — Task model → agent model → driver default must be consistent across workflow parsing, driver dispatch, and TUI display. A disagreement means the TUI shows one model while the driver uses another.\n52-\n--\n104-  readonly defaultModel: string;\n105-  healthCheck(): Promise<DriverHealth>;\n106-  dispatch(opts: DispatchOpts): AsyncIterable<StreamEvent>;\n107:  getLastCost(): number | null;\n108-}\n109-\n110-interface DispatchOpts {\n--\n145-  \"driver\": \"claude-code\",\n146-  \"model\": \"claude-opus-4\",\n147-  \"timestamp\": \"2026-04-03T10:30:00Z\",\n148:  \"cost_usd\": 0.42,\n149-  \"duration_ms\": 240000,\n150-  \"changedFiles\": [\"src/api/users.ts\", \"src/api/users.test.ts\"],\n151-  \"testResults\": { \"passed\": 12, \"failed\": 0, \"coverage\": 98.5 },\n--\n180-\n181-### Decision 5: TUI Workflow Graph Component\n182-\n183:**Decision:** New `WorkflowGraph` Ink component inserted between Header and StoryBreakdown. Renders a single-line flow with status indicators, driver labels, and cost/time per node.\n184-\n185-**Rendering format:**\n186-```\n--\n193-\n194-**Status indicators:** pending (dim), active (cyan + spinner), done (green ✓), failed (red ✗). Loop blocks show iteration count.\n195-\n196:**Rationale:** Fits existing Ink component pattern. Single-line flow is readable for workflows up to ~5 tasks. Driver and cost info below each node gives full visibility at a glance.\n197-\n198-### Decision 6: Plugin Ecosystem Pass-Through\n199-\n--\n231-export class CodexDriver implements AgentDriver {\n232-  readonly name = 'codex';\n233-  readonly defaultModel = 'codex-mini';\n234:  private lastCost: number | null = null;\n235-\n236-  async healthCheck(): Promise<DriverHealth> { /* ... */ }\n237-  async *dispatch(opts: DispatchOpts): AsyncIterable<StreamEvent> { /* ... */ }\n238:  getLastCost(): number | null { return this.lastCost; }\n239-}\n240-```\n241-\n--\n244-- Class name: `{DriverName}Driver` (PascalCase)\n245-- Export the class as named export\n246-- Register in `factory.ts` — never auto-discover\n247:- Driver MUST be stateless between dispatches (except `lastCost`)\n248-\n249-### StreamEvent Production Pattern\n250-\n--\n253-1. Zero or more `tool-start` → `tool-input` → `tool-complete` sequences\n254-2. Zero or more `text` events (interleaved with tool sequences)\n255-3. Zero or more `retry` events (if API retries occur)\n256:4. Exactly one `result` event at the end (with cost_usd and sessionId)\n257-\n258-**If the driver cannot map a CLI output line to a StreamEvent, it MUST:**\n259-- Log the unparseable line at debug level\n--\n261-- Never yield a malformed event\n262-- Never throw — unparseable lines are expected during format discovery\n263-\n264:**Cost reporting:**\n265:- If the CLI reports cost → set `result.cost_usd`\n266:- If the CLI does not report cost → set `result.cost_usd = null` (not 0, not undefined)\n267-\n268-### Error Classification Pattern\n269-\n--\n289-- Set `changedFiles` from file modification events (tool-complete for Write/Edit tools)\n290-- Set `testResults` from parsed test output (if detectable) or `null`\n291-- Set `output` as the agent's final text response\n292:- Set `cost_usd` from `getLastCost()`\n293-- Never fabricate data — if information isn't available, set `null`\n294-\n295-### Health Check Pattern\n--\n415-| Cross-Framework Execution (FR16-FR20) | `output-contract.ts`, `workflow-engine.ts` |\n416-| Plugin Integration (FR21-FR23) | Each driver's `dispatch()` (plugins → CLI flags) |\n417-| TUI Workflow Graph (FR24-FR30) | `ink-workflow.tsx`, `ink-app.tsx`, `ink-components.tsx` |\n418:| TUI Activity Extension (FR31-FR33) | `ink-renderer.tsx`, `ink-activity-components.tsx` |\n419:| Cost Tracking (FR34-FR36) | `ink-renderer.tsx`, `ink-workflow.tsx` |\n420-| Driver Capability Matrix (FR37-FR38) | `drivers/factory.ts` (capabilities metadata per driver) |\n421-\n422-### Data Flow\n--\n457-\n458-**Important Gaps (resolved):**\n459-1. Added `capabilities: DriverCapabilities` to `AgentDriver` interface for FR37-FR38\n460:2. Added `suggestCheaperDriver()` to `factory.ts` for FR36 cost routing hints\n461-\n462-### Architecture Completeness Checklist\n463-"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01FRDwwzfG8xnd7jPHer3uP2","session_id":"a0646c12-93c6-41a0-9c7a-50683cae7716","uuid":"e01c4757-b673-41e6-a98f-2b80a8d8c001","timestamp":"2026-04-03T12:48:36.296Z"}
