{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FRDwwzfG8xnd7jPHer3uP2","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Story file created. The workflow instructs me NOT to update sprint-status.yaml (user explicitly said \"Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml\"). The story is written to the correct location.\n\n---\n\n**Story Details:**\n- Story ID: 15.2\n- Story Key: 15-2-cost-tracking-per-driver\n- File: `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/15-2-cost-tracking-per-driver.md`\n- Status: ready-for-dev\n\n**What this story covers:**\n- FR8, FR33, FR34, FR35 from the multi-framework PRD\n- Per-story cost breakdown by driver in `StoryBreakdown` component (new work)\n- Per-story cost tracking in renderer state (new work)\n- `costByDriver` field on `StoryStatusEntry` (new work)\n- Run-level `driverCosts` and `DriverCostSummary` already exist — just verify no regressions\n\n**Files to change:** `ink-components.tsx` (type + component), `ink-renderer.tsx` (state tracking), plus tests in `ink-renderer.test.tsx`.\n\n**Next Steps:**\n1. Review the story at `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/15-2-cost-tracking-per-driver.md`\n2. Run `dev-story` for implementation\n3. Run `code-review` when complete\n\n---\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Problems encountered:**\n- The config.yaml at `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` does not exist; had to discover artifact locations by globbing. No impact — paths were resolved correctly from the sprint-status.yaml location.\n\n**Workarounds applied:**\n- Multiple epic files exist (`epics-multi-framework.md`, `epics-v2.md`, etc.). Identified the correct one by grepping for \"Cost Tracking Per Driver\" content. The correct source is `epics-multi-framework.md`.\n\n**Risks identified:**\n- The per-story cost snapshot mechanism requires careful design: the renderer's `updateStories()` receives story arrays from the sprint runner, but the runner doesn't currently signal \"this story just completed.\" The dev agent will need to decide between detecting status transitions in `updateStories()` or adding a dedicated method. Both are viable, but the AC doesn't prescribe which.\n- FR33 says \"per-story cost breakdown by driver in the story breakdown section\" but the epic's AC is thin (\"total cost per driver is displayed in the TUI\"). The story ACs I wrote are more specific than the epic. This is deliberate — the epic was vague.\n\n**Observations:**\n- Most of the cost infrastructure already exists from Epics 10-14. The actual new code is small: ~30 lines of production code (type extension + StoryBreakdown rendering + per-story accumulation) plus ~50 lines of tests.\n- The `DriverCostSummary` component and `driverCosts` accumulation were implemented proactively in story 14-3, so FR34/FR35 are largely already done. FR33 (per-story breakdown) is the only genuinely missing piece.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 24\n- By tool: Read: 7, Grep: 12, Glob: 4, Write: 1, Bash: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `git log --oneline -5` (~5 lines)\n- Files read: 11 unique, 13 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: None significant. Two cost-related greps on different paths could have been combined but targeted different directories for precision."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: afec62fee8b3c7d60 (use SendMessage with to: 'afec62fee8b3c7d60' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 75325\ntool_uses: 49\nduration_ms: 273933</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a0646c12-93c6-41a0-9c7a-50683cae7716","uuid":"33a62c72-1d13-490b-b46e-ed9c4c1ff3a9","timestamp":"2026-04-03T12:52:28.984Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /create-story for story 15-2-cost-tracking-per-driver. The sprint-status.yaml is at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml. Auto-discover the next backlog story and create it. For each AC, append a verification tier tag using this decision tree:\n\n**Tier Decision Tree (append one `<!-- verification: {tier} -->` tag per AC):**\n- `test-provable` — AC can be verified by building the project and running tests/linters/grep. No running app needed. Examples: 'function X exists', 'type Y is exported', 'test Z passes', 'file has <300 lines'.\n- `runtime-provable` — AC requires running the app locally and checking its behavior (CLI output, HTTP response, process lifecycle). No Docker stack needed. Examples: 'CLI prints usage when invoked with --help', 'server responds 200 on /health', 'process exits 0 on valid input'.\n- `environment-provable` — AC requires a full environment (Docker stack, database, observability, multi-service interaction). Examples: 'logs appear in VictoriaLogs', 'metrics are emitted to VictoriaMetrics', 'container communicates with service X'.\n- `escalate` — AC genuinely cannot be automated (requires physical hardware, paid external service, human visual judgment). This is rare. Examples: 'UI looks correct on mobile', 'payment processes successfully in production'.\n\nDefault to `test-provable` when unsure. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Problems encountered (errors, ambiguities in epic definition, missing context)\n- Workarounds applied (anything you did that felt hacky or suboptimal)\n- Risks identified (ACs that seem untestable, unclear requirements, missing dependencies)\n- Observations (anything surprising or noteworthy about this story)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`\n\nMANDATORY — Also end your response with a `## Token Report` section:\n- Total tool calls: N\n- By tool: Bash: X, Read: Y, Edit: Z, Grep: W, Write: V, other: N\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): command (~N lines each)\n- Files read: N unique, M total reads (list any file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: describe any repeated reads, duplicate commands, or wasted calls","agentId":"afec62fee8b3c7d60","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Story file created. The workflow instructs me NOT to update sprint-status.yaml (user explicitly said \"Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml\"). The story is written to the correct location.\n\n---\n\n**Story Details:**\n- Story ID: 15.2\n- Story Key: 15-2-cost-tracking-per-driver\n- File: `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/15-2-cost-tracking-per-driver.md`\n- Status: ready-for-dev\n\n**What this story covers:**\n- FR8, FR33, FR34, FR35 from the multi-framework PRD\n- Per-story cost breakdown by driver in `StoryBreakdown` component (new work)\n- Per-story cost tracking in renderer state (new work)\n- `costByDriver` field on `StoryStatusEntry` (new work)\n- Run-level `driverCosts` and `DriverCostSummary` already exist — just verify no regressions\n\n**Files to change:** `ink-components.tsx` (type + component), `ink-renderer.tsx` (state tracking), plus tests in `ink-renderer.test.tsx`.\n\n**Next Steps:**\n1. Review the story at `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/15-2-cost-tracking-per-driver.md`\n2. Run `dev-story` for implementation\n3. Run `code-review` when complete\n\n---\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Problems encountered:**\n- The config.yaml at `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` does not exist; had to discover artifact locations by globbing. No impact — paths were resolved correctly from the sprint-status.yaml location.\n\n**Workarounds applied:**\n- Multiple epic files exist (`epics-multi-framework.md`, `epics-v2.md`, etc.). Identified the correct one by grepping for \"Cost Tracking Per Driver\" content. The correct source is `epics-multi-framework.md`.\n\n**Risks identified:**\n- The per-story cost snapshot mechanism requires careful design: the renderer's `updateStories()` receives story arrays from the sprint runner, but the runner doesn't currently signal \"this story just completed.\" The dev agent will need to decide between detecting status