{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KuW1MjUdFwtjdSVSiFS3H5","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Story 15-2 is complete. All 8 tasks and all subtasks are marked done. Status is set to \"review\".\n\n**Summary of changes:**\n\n1. **`src/lib/ink-components.tsx`** (226 lines) -- Added `costByDriver?: Record<string, number>` to `StoryStatusEntry`. Updated `StoryBreakdown` to render per-driver cost breakdown on done stories (format: `1-1 ✓ claude-code $0.42, codex $0.15`, sorted alphabetically, excluded when empty/undefined).\n\n2. **`src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx`** (299 lines) -- Added `currentStoryCosts` and `lastStoryKey` internal tracking. Per-story costs accumulate on `result` events alongside existing run-level `driverCosts`. Costs are snapshotted onto `StoryStatusEntry.costByDriver` when a story transitions to done in `updateStories()`. Costs reset when the story key changes via `updateSprintState()` or `updateStories()`.\n\n3. **`src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx`** (1116 lines) -- Added 10 new tests in two describe blocks: `StoryBreakdown per-story cost display` (6 tests) and `per-story cost accumulation (controller integration)` (4 tests).\n\n**Build:** 0 TypeScript errors. **Tests:** 4624 passed, 0 regressions, 10 new.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- The test file `ink-renderer.test.tsx` is at 1116 lines, well above 300. However, this is a test file and the 300-line constraint in AC #10 says \"every source file\" -- the existing test file was already ~993 lines before this story. No source files exceed 300 lines.\n- `ink-renderer.tsx` needed trimming from 315 to 299 lines to stay under the limit. Shortened the file-level doc comment. This is tight -- any future additions will need careful line management or extraction of helpers.\n- The per-story cost snapshotting logic in `updateStories()` relies on matching `state.sprintInfo.storyKey` against story entry keys. If the caller passes stories with different key formats (e.g., short key vs full key), the match won't work. This mirrors the existing pattern throughout the codebase, so it's consistent but worth noting.\n- Controller integration tests verify no crashes but cannot directly assert internal state (currentStoryCosts). The StoryBreakdown component tests provide the observable-output verification instead.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 32\n- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 7, Edit: 18, Grep: 1, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npm run test:unit` (~50 lines each, x2), `npm run build` (~15 lines, x2)\n- Files read: 7 unique, 8 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: The 18 Edit calls for marking subtask checkboxes could have been fewer if `replace_all` covered all subtask patterns at once, but the patterns were distinct enough to require individual calls. Two build runs and two test runs (pre- and post-refactor) were necessary to verify correctness."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aff60e4739d4aea05 (use SendMessage with to: 'aff60e4739d4aea05' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 71570\ntool_uses: 54\nduration_ms: 298759</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a0646c12-93c6-41a0-9c7a-50683cae7716","uuid":"4ed9910c-82d6-41fa-b9be-307850e3c361","timestamp":"2026-04-03T12:59:47.348Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-dev-story for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/15-2-cost-tracking-per-driver.md — implement all tasks, write tests, and mark the story for review. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously through all tasks until complete. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Problems encountered (build failures, test failures, unclear task specs, missing APIs)\n- Workarounds applied (anything hacky, copied patterns that felt wrong, TODOs left behind)\n- Code quality 