{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FXbxFTW7bzJr4gL7DWdcAa","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**CODE REVIEW FINDINGS**\n\n**Story:** `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/15-2-cost-tracking-per-driver.md`\n**Git vs Story Discrepancies:** 0 (all changed files match story File List)\n**Issues Found:** 2 High, 2 Medium, 1 Low\n\n**HIGH Issues (fixed):**\n1. **Cost-loss bug on story key change** — When `updateSprintState` changed the story key, `currentStoryCosts` was reset before `updateStories` had a chance to snapshot costs onto the completing story. Old story's costs were silently discarded. Fixed by introducing `pendingStoryCosts` map that freezes costs on key change and lets `updateStories` pick them up later.\n\n2. **Controller tests had zero assertions** — All 4 controller integration tests just verified \"no crash\" with no `expect()` calls on actual cost values. The cost snapshotting logic was entirely untested. Fixed by adding real assertions using new `_getState()` test hook, including exact cost value checks on `costByDriver`.\n\n**MEDIUM Issues (fixed):**\n3. **Caller object mutation** — `updateStories()` directly mutated the caller's `StoryStatusEntry` objects by setting `s.costByDriver`. Fixed by using `stories.map()` and returning new objects via spread.\n\n4. **File over 300 lines** — `ink-renderer.tsx` was 321 lines, violating AC #10 (300-line limit). Fixed by extracting `promoteActiveTool()` helper and compacting the cleanup/signal handlers. Now 284 lines.\n\n**LOW Issue (not fixed):**\n5. **`_getState` optional method pattern** — Using `_getState?()` on the interface means callers must use `handle._getState!()`. A separate `TestRendererHandle` interface extending `RendererHandle` would be cleaner but is not worth the churn.\n\n**Review Complete:** Status set to `verifying`. 4 issues fixed. All 4625 tests pass. Build clean. Coverage 96.85%, all files above 80%.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and their severity:**\n- HIGH: Cost-loss on story key change — `updateSprintState` reset `currentStoryCosts` before `updateStories` could snapshot, silently dropping accumulated costs for the completing story\n- HIGH: Controller integration tests had zero value assertions — cost snapshotting logic was effectively untested despite 4 tests existing\n- MEDIUM: `updateStories()` mutated caller-owned `StoryStatusEntry` objects directly\n- MEDIUM: `ink-renderer.tsx` at 321 lines violated 300-line AC\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed:**\n- LOW: `_getState?()` optional method pattern on `RendererHandle` interface — a separate test-only interface would be cleaner\n- LOW: `pendingStoryCosts` is a `Map` while `currentStoryCosts` and `driverCosts` are plain objects — inconsistent collection types (Map is fine here for key-based deletion but breaks the pattern)\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- None — 96.85% overall, all 171 files above 80% floor\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- The per-story cost tracking spans two methods (`updateSprintState` and `updateStories`) creating ordering-dependent behavior. A single explicit `finalizeStory(key)` method would be more robust but would require changes to the sprint runner caller.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None — all HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed in this review session\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 24\n- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 9, Edit: 8, Grep: 0, Write: 0, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npm run test:unit -- --reporter=verbose | grep` (~30 lines), `git diff` (~170 lines), `npm run test:unit | tail -5` (~5 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 12 total reads (ink-renderer.test.tsx read 4 times due to size limits)\n- Redundant operations: ink-renderer.test.tsx was read in 4 chunks due to token limit — could have been more targeted with offset/limit from the start. Two separate build checks were needed (pre-fix and post-fix). Two coverage runs were needed (pre-fix verification and post-fix confirmation)."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ae6a1e60ba7644463 (use SendMessage with to: 'ae6a1e60ba7644463' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 77014\ntool_uses: 48\nduration_ms: 361852</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a0646c12-93c6-41a0-9c7a-50683cae7716","uuid":"b5ab82a3-9c74-4196-8e49-697795e8bff2","timestamp":"2026-04-03T13:06:27.136Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/15-2-cost-tracking-per-driver.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` and ensure all files pass the per-file floor and the overall 90% target. Update the story status to `verifying` when all issues are fixed and coverage passes. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Bugs found and their severity (HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW with brief description)\n- Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority items, tech debt)\n- Coverage gaps (files below floor, untested edge cases, areas needing integration tests)\n- Architecture concerns (patterns that don't fit, coupling issues, missing abstractions)\n- Items sent back for re-development (what failed and why)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`\n\nMANDATORY — Also end your response with a `## Token Report` section:\n- Total tool calls: N\n- By tool: Bash: X, Read: Y, Edit: Z, Grep: W, Write: V, other: N\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): command (~N lines each)\n- Files read: N unique, M total reads (list any file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: describe any repeated reads, duplicate commands, or wasted calls","agentId":"ae6a1e60ba7644463","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\