hot, silently dropping accumulated costs for the completing story\n- HIGH: Controller integration tests had zero value assertions — cost snapshotting logic was effectively untested despite 4 tests existing\n- MEDIUM: `updateStories()` mutated caller-owned `StoryStatusEntry` objects directly\n- MEDIUM: `ink-renderer.tsx` at 321 lines violated 300-line AC\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed:**\n- LOW: `_getState?()` optional method pattern on `RendererHandle` interface — a separate test-only interface would be cleaner\n- LOW: `pendingStoryCosts` is a `Map` while `currentStoryCosts` and `driverCosts` are plain objects — inconsistent collection types (Map is fine here for key-based deletion but breaks the pattern)\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- None — 96.85% overall, all 171 files above 80% floor\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- The per-story cost tracking spans two methods (`updateSprintState` and `updateStories`) creating ordering-dependent behavior. A single explicit `finalizeStory(key)` method would be more robust but would require changes to the sprint runner caller.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None — all HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed in this review session\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 24\n- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 9, Edit: 8, Grep: 0, Write: 0, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npm run test:unit -- --reporter=verbose | grep` (~30 lines), `git diff` (~170 lines), `npm run test:unit | tail -5` (~5 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 12 total reads (ink-renderer.test.tsx read 4 times due to size limits)\n- Redundant operations: ink-renderer.test.tsx was read in 4 chunks due to token limit — could have been more targeted with offset/limit from the start. Two separate build checks were needed (pre-fix and post-fix). Two coverage runs were needed (pre-fix verification and post-fix confirmation)."}],"totalDurationMs":361852,"totalTokens":77014,"totalToolUseCount":48,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_inp