{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VJZWXmVxgE8ikuJxxtZSBN","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 15.2: Cost Tracking Per Driver\n2\t\n3\tStatus: verifying\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a user,\n10\tI want to see accumulated cost per driver across a workflow run and per-story cost breakdown by driver in the TUI,\n11\tso that I can compare framework costs and optimize my workflow configurations.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** a multi-driver workflow run where tasks complete on `claude-code` and `codex` drivers\n16\t   **When** each task's result event includes `cost_usd`\n17\t   **Then** the workflow engine accumulates cost per driver name in a `Record<string, number>` structure\n18\t   **And** the accumulated totals are accessible to the TUI renderer\n19\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n20\t\n21\t2. **Given** accumulated per-driver costs exist after task completions\n22\t   **When** the TUI renders the `DriverCostSummary` component\n23\t   **Then** total cost per driver is displayed as `Cost: claude-code $X.XX, codex $Y.YY` (sorted alphabetically by driver name)\n24\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n25\t\n26\t3. **Given** a driver that does not report cost (e.g., `cost_usd` is null in its result event)\n27\t   **When** the TUI displays per-driver cost totals\n28\t   **Then** that driver is excluded from the cost summary (it does not show `$0.00`)\n29\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n30\t\n31\t4. **Given** a workflow run with multiple stories each using different drivers\n32\t   **When** the TUI renders the `StoryBreakdown` section for completed stories\n33\t   **Then** each completed story line shows its per-driver cost breakdown (e.g., `1-1 ✓ claude-code $0.42, codex $0.15`)\n34\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n35\t\n36\t5. **Given** a completed story where only one driver was used\n37\t   **When** the TUI renders the story breakdown\n38\t   **Then** the story line shows cost for that single driver (e.g., `1-1 ✓ claude-code $0.42`)\n39\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n40\t\n41\t6. **Given** a completed story where no driver reported cost\n42\t   **When** the TUI renders the story breakdown\n43\t   **Then** the story line shows the status without any cost annotation (e.g., `1-1 ✓`)\n44\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n45\t\n46\t7. **Given** multiple result events arrive for the same driver within the same story\n47\t   **When** the renderer accumulates costs\n48\t   **Then** costs are summed (not replaced) per driver per story\n49\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n50\t\n51\t8. **Given** `npm run build` is executed after all changes\n52\t   **When** the build completes\n53\t   **Then** it succeeds with zero TypeScript errors\n54\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n55\t\n56\t9. **Given** `npm run test:unit` is executed after all changes\n57\t   **When** the tests complete\n58\t   **Then** all existing tests pass with zero regressions\n59\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n60\t\n61\t10. **Given** no new file exceeds 300 lines\n62\t    **When** line count is checked for all modified/created files\n63\t    **Then** every source file stays under 300 lines\n64\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n65\t\n66\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n67\t\n68\t- [x] Task 1 (AC: #4, #5, #6, #7): Add per-story cost tracking to `RendererState` and `StoryStatusEntry`\n69\t  - [x] In `src/lib/ink-components.tsx`, add `costByDriver?: Record<string, number>` to `StoryStatusEntry` interface\n70\t  - [x] In `src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx`, add `currentStoryCosts: Record<string, number>` to internal state tracking\n71\t  - [x] On each `result` event with `cost > 0` and `driverName`, accumulate into `currentStoryCosts[driverName]`\n72\t  - [x] Expose a method or mechanism for the sprint runner to snapshot `currentStoryCosts` when a story completes and attach it to the `StoryStatusEntry`\n73\t  - [x] Reset `currentStoryCosts` when a new story starts (on `updateStories` or `updateSprintState` with a new `storyKey`)\n74\t\n75\t- [x] Task 2 (AC: #4, #5, #6): Update `StoryBreakdown` to display per-story cost breakdown\n76\t  - [x] In `src/lib/ink-components.tsx`, modify `StoryBreakdown` to render cost info for done stories\n77\t  - [x] For each done story with `costByDriver` entries: append formatted cost string after the `✓` marker\n78\t  - [x] Format: `shortKey ✓ driver1 $X.XX, driver2 $Y.YY` (sorted alphabetically)\n79\t  - [x] If `costByDriver` is empty or undefined, render just `shortKey ✓` (no cost annotation)\n80\t\n81\t- [x] Task 3 (AC: #1, #2, #3): Verify existing `driverCosts` accumulation in `ink-renderer.tsx`\n82\t  - [x] Confirm `driverCosts` accumulation already works correctly for run-level totals (existing code at lines 215-221)\n83\t  - [x] Confirm `DriverCostSummary` already renders total cost per driver (existing component)\n84\t  - [x] Confirm drivers with null cost are excluded (existing: `event.cost > 0` guard)\n85\t  - [x] Add tests if any gaps found\n86\t\n87\t- [x] Task 4 (AC: #1, #7): Write unit tests for per-story cost accumulation\n88\t  - [x] Test: result events from multiple drivers accumulate per-story costs correctly\n89\t  - [x] Test: multiple result events from same driver within one story sum correctly\n90\t  - [x] Test: story cost resets when new story starts\n91\t  - [x] Test: null/zero cost events do not create entries\n92\t\n93\t- [x] Task 5 (AC: #4, #5, #6): Write unit tests for StoryBreakdown cost display\n94\t  - [x] Test: done story with multi-driver costs shows breakdown\n95\t  - [x] Test: done story with single-driver cost shows that driver\n96\t  - [x] Test: done story with no cost data shows just the checkmark\n97\t  - [x] Test: cost format uses `$X.XX` pattern\n98\t\n99\t- [x] Task 6 (AC: #8): Run `npm run build` — zero TypeScript errors\n100\t- [x] Task 7 (AC: #9): Run `npm run test:unit` — all tests pass, zero regressions\n101\t- [x] Task 8 (AC: #10): Verify all modified files are under 300 lines\n102\t\n103\t## Dev Notes\n104\t\n105\t### Architecture Compliance\n106\t\n107\tThis story implements Epic 6, Story 6.2 (mapped to sprint Epic 15, Story 15-2) \"Cost Tracking Per Driver\" from `epics-multi-framework.md`. It covers:\n108\t- **FR8:** System can capture cost information from driver output and normalize to cost_usd\n109\t- **FR33:** System can display per-story cost breakdown by driver in the story breakdown section\n110\t- **FR34:** System can accumulate cost per driver across a workflow run\n111\t- **FR35:** System can display total cost per driver in the TUI\n112\t\n113\tKey architecture decisions honored:\n114\t- **Decision 1 (AgentDriver interface):** `getLastCost(): number | null` — already on all drivers\n115\t- **Decision 5 (TUI Workflow Graph):** Cost/time per node in workflow graph — already implemented\n116\t- **Cost reporting pattern:** `cost_usd = null` (not 0) when driver doesn't report cost\n117\t\n118\t### What Already Exists (from previous epics)\n119\t\n120\t**Run-level cost accumulation is fully implemented.** The plumbing:\n121\t\n122\t1. **All 3 drivers** implement `getLastCost()` and set `lastCost` from result events\n123\t2. **StreamEvent result events** carry `cost` and `cost_usd` fields\n124\t3. **`ink-renderer.tsx` lines 215-221:** `driverCosts` accumulation on `result` events with `driverName`\n125\t4. **`DriverCostSummary` component** (`ink-activity-components.tsx` line 104): renders `Cost: driver1 $X.XX, driver2 $Y.YY`\n126\t5. **`ink-app.tsx` line 24:** `DriverCostSummary` is rendered in the App layout\n127\t6. **`RendererState.driverCosts`** (`ink-components.tsx` line 77): `Record<string, number>`\n128\t7. **Workflow graph** (`ink-workflow.tsx`): `formatCost()` shows cost per task node\n129\t8. **Output contract** (`types.ts` line 74): `cost_usd: number | null` per task\n130\t9. **Existing tests** in `ink-renderer.test.tsx` and `ink-activity-components.test.tsx` cover run-level accumulation\n131\t\n132\t**What's missing (the actual work for this story):**\n133\t\n134\t1. **Per-story cost breakdown in `StoryBreakdown`** — FR33 says \"per-story cost breakdown by driver in the story breakdown section.\" The `StoryBreakdown` component currently shows story status only (done/in-progress/pending/failed/blocked) with NO cost information.\n135\t2. **Per-story cost tracking in renderer state** — `currentStoryCosts` per story is not tracked. The renderer accumulates `driverCosts` across the entire run but doesn't partition by story.\n136\t3. **`StoryStatusEntry` lacks cost data** — The interface has `key`, `status`, `retryCount`, `maxRetries` but no cost fields.\n137\t\n138\t### Data Flow (New)\n139\t\n140\t```\n141\tresult event { cost: 0.42 } + driverName='claude-code'\n142\t     ↓\n143\tink-renderer.update(event, 'claude-code')\n144\t     ↓\n145\t  state.driverCosts['claude-code'] += 0.42   (existing — run-level total)\n146\t  state.currentStoryCosts['claude-code'] += 0.42   (NEW — per-story accumulation)\n147\t     ↓\n148\tWhen story completes → snapshot currentStoryCosts into StoryStatusEntry.costByDriver\n149\t     ↓\n150\tStoryBreakdown renders: \"1-1 ✓ claude-code $0.42\"\n151\t```\n152\t\n153\t### Implementation Approach\n154\t\n155\tThe cleanest approach: add `costByDriver` to `StoryStatusEntry`, track `currentStoryCosts` in the renderer's closure, and snapshot it onto stories when `updateStories()` is called with a status change from in-progress to done.\n156\t\n157\tThe `updateStories()` method already receives the full stories array. When it detects a story that just moved to `done` status, it can attach `currentStoryCosts` and reset.\n158\t\n159\tAlternative: The sprint runner (in `src/commands/run.ts`) could attach cost data to `StoryStatusEntry` before passing it to `updateStories()`. This would keep the renderer dumber but requires the runner to track per-story costs. Given the renderer already has `driverCosts` accumulation, extending it with per-story tracking is more cohesive.\n160\t\n161\t### What NOT to Do\n162\t\n163\t- Do NOT modify any driver files — cost reporting is already correct\n164\t- Do NOT modify `DispatchOpts`, `OutputContract`, or `AgentDriver` interface — they already support cost\n165\t- Do NOT modify the workflow engine's `dispatchTaskWithResult` — it already reads `cost` from events correctly\n166\t- Do NOT change the workflow graph component — per-task cost/time is already displayed there\n167\t- Do NOT modify `DriverCostSummary` — run-level totals are already correct\n168\t- Do NOT add new npm dependencies\n169\t- Do NOT attempt to merge per-story costs and run-level costs — they serve different purposes\n170\t\n171\t### Line Budget Analysis\n172\t\n173\t| File | Current Lines | Estimated Change | Target |\n174\t|------|--------------|------------------|--------|\n175\t| `ink-components.tsx` | ~215 | +15 (StoryStatusEntry + StoryBreakdown cost) | ~230 |\n176\t| `ink-renderer.tsx` | ~250 | +15 (currentStoryCosts tracking) | ~265 |\n177\t| Tests (various) | — | +40-60 (new test cases) | within budget |\n178\t\n179\tAll source files stay well under 300 lines.\n180\t\n181\t### Testing Guidance\n182\t\n183\t- **Vitest** (not Jest). Use `vi.fn()`, `vi.mock()`, `vi.mocked()`.\n184\t- For `StoryBreakdown` cost display: extend `src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx` or the component-level tests\n185\t- For per-story cost accumulation: extend `src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx` `describe('driver name in update()')` section\n186\t- For `DriverCostSummary`: existing tests in `src/lib/__tests__/ink-activity-components.test.tsx` already pass — verify no regressions\n187\t- Pattern: follow the existing `driverCosts` accumulation tests as a template for per-story cost tests\n188\t- Render tests use `ink-testing-library` `render()` and `lastFrame()`\n189\t\n190\t### Previous Story Intelligence (15-1)\n191\t\n192\t- Story 15-1 added agent-level plugin configuration. Pattern: extend interfaces first (add to types), then wire into the system, then tests.\n193\t- 4614 tests at end of 15-1. Expect to add ~10-15 new tests.\n194\t- Build is clean. TypeScript strict mode is on.\n195\t- The test suite is large. Add tests sparingly — focus on new behavior (per-story cost in StoryBreakdown, currentStoryCosts tracking).\n196\t\n197\t### Git Intelligence\n198\t\n199\tLast commits:\n200\t- `dcaf19b feat: story 15-1-plugin-pass-through-configuration — Plugin Pass-Through Configuration`\n201\t- `8272ef0 feat: epic 14 complete`\n202\t\n203\tPattern from story 15-1: stories that extend existing plumbing (type extension → state wiring → component update → tests) complete cleanly in one pass.\n204\t\n205\t### References\n206\t\n207\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-multi-framework.md#Story 6.2: Cost Tracking Per Driver]\n208\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md — Cost reporting pattern, Decision 1, Decision 5]\n209\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md — FR8, FR33, FR34, FR35]\n210\t- [Source: src/lib/ink-components.tsx — StoryBreakdown component, StoryStatusEntry interface, RendererState]\n211\t- [Source: src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx — driverCosts accumulation, update() function, startRenderer()]\n212\t- [Source: src/lib/ink-activity-components.tsx — DriverCostSummary component]\n213\t- [Source: src/lib/ink-app.tsx — App layout with DriverCostSummary placement]\n214\t- [Source: src/lib/ink-workflow.tsx — formatCost(), per-task cost in workflow graph]\n215\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/types.ts — AgentDriver.getLastCost(), OutputContract.cost_usd, DriverCapabilities.costReporting]\n216\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/drivers/claude-code.ts — lastCost tracking, getLastCost()]\n217\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/drivers/codex.ts — lastCost tracking, getLastCost()]\n218\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/drivers/opencode.ts — lastCost tracking, getLastCost()]\n219\t\n220\t## Files to Change\n221\t\n222\t- `src/lib/ink-components.tsx` — Add `costByDriver?: Record<string, number>` to `StoryStatusEntry`; update `StoryBreakdown` to render per-story cost\n223\t- `src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx` — Add `currentStoryCosts` tracking; snapshot into stories on completion; reset on new story\n224\t- `src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx` — Add tests for per-story cost accumulation and story breakdown cost display\n225\t- `src/lib/__tests__/ink-activity-components.test.tsx` — Verify existing DriverCostSummary tests still pass (no new tests expected)\n226\t\n227\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n228\t## Verification Requirements\n229\t\n230\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/15-2-cost-tracking-per-driver-proof.md)\n231\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n232\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n233\t\n234\t## Documentation Requirements\n235\t\n236\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n237\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/15-2-cost-tracking-per-driver.md\n238\t\n239\t## Testing Requirements\n240\t\n241\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n242\t- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n243\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n244\t\n245\t## Dev Agent Record\n246\t\n247\t### Agent Model Used\n248\t\n249\tClaude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n250\t\n251\t### Debug Log References\n252\t\n253\t### Completion Notes List\n254\t\n255\t- Added `costByDriver?: Record<string, number>` to `StoryStatusEntry` interface\n256\t- Added `currentStoryCosts` and `lastStoryKey` internal tracking to ink-renderer controller\n257\t- Per-story cost accumulation on result events with driverName, snapshotted onto StoryStatusEntry when story transitions to done, reset on story key change\n258\t- Updated `StoryBreakdown` to render per-story cost breakdown after checkmark for done stories, sorted alphabetically by driver name\n259\t- Verified existing `driverCosts` run-level accumulation and `DriverCostSummary` still work correctly (no changes needed)\n260\t- 10 new tests: 6 for StoryBreakdown cost display, 4 for per-story cost accumulation controller integration\n261\t- Build: 0 TypeScript errors. Tests: 4624 passed, 0 regressions. All files under 300 lines.\n262\t\n263\t### Change Log\n264\t\n265\t- 2026-04-03: Story created with 10 ACs covering FR8, FR33, FR34, FR35. Per-story cost breakdown in StoryBreakdown is the primary new work; run-level driverCosts accumulation and DriverCostSummary already exist from Epics 10-14. Status set to ready-for-dev.\n266\t- 2026-04-03: Implementation complete. Per-story cost tracking added to renderer, StoryBreakdown updated to display per-driver costs on done stories, 10 tests added. Status set to review.\n267\t- 2026-04-03: Code review fixes — Fixed cost-loss bug on story key change (costs for old story were discarded when updateSprintState changed the key before updateStories could snapshot them). Introduced pendingStoryCosts map to properly freeze per-story costs on key change. Fixed caller object mutation in updateStories. Added _getState() test hook. Upgraded controller integration tests from crash-only to value-asserting. Extracted promoteActiveTool helper to reduce ink-renderer.tsx from 321 to 284 lines. Status set to verifying.\n268\t\n269\t### File List\n270\t\n271\t- src/lib/ink-components.tsx (modified — added costByDriver to StoryStatusEntry, updated StoryBreakdown cost rendering)\n272\t- src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx (modified — added currentStoryCosts tracking, snapshot on story completion, reset on story change)\n273\t- src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx (modified — added 10 new tests for per-story cost display and accumulation)\n274\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014gLZjroZpgCZ3ggEGkkW4f","session_id":"a0646c12-93c6-41a0-9c7a-50683cae7716","uuid":"68bf5eef-a08b-4c04-afa9-900b8da3cfe2","timestam