{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01981V5VqvjZRCY78xWtHANq","type":"tool_result","content":"0\t# Session Retrospective — 2026-04-03\n1\t\n2\t**Session window:** ~2026-04-03T00:25 to ~2026-04-03T02:00 (approx. 95 minutes)\n3\t**Sprint progress:** 14/28 stories done (50%), Epics 1-4 complete\n4\t\n5\t---\n6\t\n7\t## 1. Session Summary\n8\t\n9\t| Story | Phases Run | Outcome | Notes |\n10\t|-------|-----------|---------|-------|\n11\t| 4-3-trace-id-generation-injection | verify (tail end) | **Done** | Was already at verify from prior session. 9/9 ACs passed. |\n12\t| 4-4-source-isolation-enforcement | create-story, dev, code-review, verify | **Done** | Full lifecycle in one session. 9/9 ACs, 100% coverage on module. |\n13\t| Epic 4 milestone | — | **Done** | All 4 stories shipped. Commit `4a35568`. |\n14\t| 5-1-flow-execution-sequential-steps | create-story, dev | **Review** | Story created and implemented. 31 tests, 89.91% coverage. Ran out of time before code-review/verify. |\n15\t\n16\t**Net output:** 2 stories completed + verified, 1 story implemented but not reviewed, 1 epic closed.\n17\t\n18\t---\n19\t\n20\t## 2. Issues Analysis\n21\t\n22\t### Bugs Found by Code Review (fixed)\n23\t\n24\t| Severity | Story | Issue |\n25\t|----------|-------|-------|\n26\t| HIGH | 4-3 | `generateTraceId` accepted NaN/Infinity/negative/float iteration values |\n27\t| HIGH | 4-4 | Path traversal via unsanitized `runId` in file path |\n28\t| HIGH | 4-4 | Silent file overwrite on basename collision — data loss risk |\n29\t| MEDIUM | 4-3 | No segment length cap — unbounded trace IDs possible |\n30\t| MEDIUM | 4-3 | `formatTracePrompt('')` produced empty trace marker silently |\n31\t| MEDIUM | 4-3 | `workflow-state.ts` coverage at 79.06%, below 80% floor |\n32\t| MEDIUM | 4-4 | Stale workspace contamination from crashed runs |\n33\t| MEDIUM | 4-4 | Missing edge case tests for sanitization/dedup |\n34\t\n35\tAll HIGH and MEDIUM bugs were fixed in the same session. Code review is earning its keep — 3 HIGH security/correctness bugs caught before merge.\n36\t\n37\t### Known LOW Issues (deferred)\n38\t\n39\t- 4-3: Duplicate trace ID guard missing; empty runId+taskName produces ugly ID; sanitizeSegment strips non-ASCII\n40\t- 4-4: `deduplicateFilename` counter loop unbounded; hardcoded `/tmp/` base path\n41\t\n42\t### Infrastructure Issues\n43\t\n44\t- **`codeharness verify` precondition failure:** The verify command checks global harness state flags (`tests_passed`, `coverage_met`) which are not set by manual test runs. Workaround: verify manually. This is a harness tooling gap.\n45\t- **`AGENTS.md` stale:** Verify command flags missing entries for new modules (`agent-dispatch.ts`, `agent-resolver.ts`, `session-manager.ts`, `trace-id.ts`, `source-isolation.ts`). Documentation debt accumulating — 5 modules behind now.\n46\t- **Pre-existing TS errors:** `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` has 2 pre-existing type errors unrelated to current work.\n47\t\n48\t---\n49\t\n50\t## 3. Cost Analysis\n51\t\n52\t### Parent-Level Costs (from cost-report.md, prior session data)\n53\t\n54\tThe cost report covers the prior session (stories through Epic 2). Key structural observations:\n55\t\n56\t- **Total API cost:** $37.08 across 288 calls for 7 stories\n57\t- **Avg cost/story:** $4.45\n58\t- **Dominant cost:** Cache reads at 61% ($22.62) — expected for long-context sessions\n59\t- **Verify phase:** 43.8% of total cost ($16.24) — nearly half of all spending is on verification\n60\t\n61\t### Subagent Token Report (this session)\n62\t\n63\tAggregated from `.session-issues.md` token reports:\n64\t\n65\t| Subagent Phase | Tool Calls | Top Tools |\n66\t|---------------|------------|-----------|\n67\t| 4-3 create-story | 14 | Read: 5, Grep: 4, Glob: 3 |\n68\t| 4-3 dev-story | 14 | Edit: 6, Read: 5, Bash: 4 |\n69\t| 4-3 code-review | 23 | Bash: 12, Read: 7, Edit: 5 |\n70\t| 4-3 verification | 12 | Bash: 7, Read: 3, Grep: 2 |\n71\t| 4-4 create-story | 12 | Read: 7, Grep: 3 |\n72\t| 4-4 dev-story | 15 | Read: 5, Bash: 4, Grep: 4 |\n73\t| 4-4 code-review | 22 | Bash: 9, Read: 7, Edit: 7 |\n74\t| 4-4 verification | 12 | Bash: 7, Read: 3, Grep: 2 |\n75\t| 5-1 create-story | 18 | Read: 12, Glob: 5, Bash: 2 |\n76\t| 5-1 dev-story | 22 | Read: 13, Bash: 6, Edit: 4 |\n77\t| **Total** | **164** | Read: 67, Bash: 51, Edit: 22, Grep: 18 |\n78\t\n79\t### Observations\n80\t\n81\t- **Code review is the most tool-heavy phase** (22-23 calls) — Bash-heavy because it runs tests after each fix.\n82\t- **Read dominates** at 67/164 calls (41%). The 5-1 create-story phase read 12 unique files — story creation requires reading architecture, PRD, epics, and existing modules.\n83\t- **Redundant operations detected:**\n84\t  - 4-3 verification: `codeharness verify` called twice\n85\t  - 4-4 verification: Coverage run twice (default + targeted)\n86\t  - 4-4 create-story: Two Grep calls to `source_access` could have been one\n87\t  - 4-3 verification: Architecture doc `architecture-v2.md` read twice\n88\t- **Largest Bash outputs:** Coverage runs (80-160 lines) dominate. Test suite runs are 20-50 lines.\n89\t\n90\t### Estimated session cost\n91\t\n92\tAt ~164 subagent tool calls plus orchestrator overhead, estimated this session cost **$10-14** (extrapolating from prior session's $4.45/story rate, 2.5 story-equivalents completed).\n93\t\n94\t---\n95\t\n96\t## 4. What Went Well\n97\t\n98\t1. **Full-lifecycle velocity:** Story 4-4 went from backlog to verified in a single session (~45 min for create+dev+review+verify). The pipeline is working.\n99\t2. **Code review catching real bugs:** 3 HIGH severity bugs caught (path traversal, data loss, input validation). These would have been production defects.\n100\t3. **Epic 4 completed:** All 4 stories (agent dispatch, session management, trace IDs, source isolation) shipped and verified.\n101\t4. **Test quality:** 100% coverage on both trace-id.ts and source-isolation.ts modules. 31 tests written for 5-1 in dev phase alone.\n102\t5. **Zero retries this session:** All stories completed on first attempt — no stuck/failed cycles.\n103\t6. **Session issues log is working:** Subagent self-reporting produced actionable data for this retro.\n104\t\n105\t---\n106\t\n107\t## 5. What Went Wrong\n108\t\n109\t1. **Time budget exhaustion:** Story 5-1 got through dev but couldn't complete code-review or verify. It's stuck at \"review\" status — needs manual follow-up.\n110\t2. **`codeharness verify` is unreliable:** Fails on harness state flags that aren't set during subagent runs. This forced manual verification workarounds in both 4-3 and 4-4.\n111\t3. **AGENTS.md documentation debt:** 5 new modules have no AGENTS.md entries. The verify command flags this every time, burning cycles on a known-stale doc.\n112\t4. **Cost report stale:** `codeharness stats --save` requires `session-logs/` directory which doesn't exist for this session type. The cost report only covers the prior session's data.\n113\t5. **Sprint state file divergence:** `ralph/.state-snapshot.json` shows 4-4 as \"verifying\" and 5-1 as \"backlog\" — but sprint-status.yaml shows 4-4 as done and 5-1 as review. State files are out of sync.\n114\t\n115\t---\n116\t\n117\t## 6. Lessons Learned\n118\t\n119\t### Patterns to Repeat\n120\t\n121\t- **Code review as a mandatory gate:** Every HIGH bug this session was caught by code review, not tests. The adversarial review phase is load-bearing.\n122\t- **Session issues log:** Self-reported token data from subagents made cost analysis possible without working harness stats.\n123\t- **Pure-logic module design:** Both trace-id and source-isolation achieved 100% coverage because they have no I/O dependencies. This pattern works.\n124\t\n125\t### Patterns to Avoid\n126\t\n127\t- **Running `codeharness verify` without checking preconditions:** Wastes a full invocation cycle. Either fix the verify command or skip it when flags aren't set.\n128\t- **Running coverage twice:** Once is enough. The second targeted run is redundant when the first already reports per-file coverage.\n129\t- **Starting a new story late in a session:** 5-1 was started knowing time was short. It would have been cleaner to stop after Epic 4 closure.\n130\t\n131\t---\n132\t\n133\t## 7. Action Items\n134\t\n135\t| # | Action | Priority | Owner |\n136\t|---|--------|----------|-------|\n137\t| 1 | Complete code-review and verify for story 5-1 | HIGH | Next session |\n138\t| 2 | Fix `codeharness verify` to work without pre-set harness state flags | MEDIUM | Backlog |\n139\t| 3 | Update `src/lib/AGENTS.md` with entries for agent-dispatch, agent-resolver, session-manager, trace-id, source-isolation modules | MEDIUM | Next session |\n140\t| 4 | Fix `codeharness stats --save` to work for non-ralph sessions | LOW | Backlog |\n141\t| 5 | Sync `ralph/.state-snapshot.json` with `sprint-state.json` | LOW | Next session |\n142\t| 6 | Fix pre-existing TS errors in `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` | LOW | Backlog |\n143\t| 7 | Address deferred LOW issues from 4-3 and 4-4 code reviews | LOW | Backlog |\n144\t\n145\t---\n146\t\n147\t# Session Retrospective — 2026-04-03 (Session 2)\n148\t\n149\t**Timestamp:** 2026-04-03T02:00Z\n150\t**Session window:** ~2026-04-03T01:53 to ~2026-04-03T02:15 (approx. 22 minutes)\n151\t**Sprint progress:** 15/28 stories done (53.6%), Epics 1-4 complete, Epic 5 started\n152\t\n153\t---\n154\t\n155\t## 1. Session Summary\n156\t\n157\tThis session picked up story 5-1-flow-execution-sequential-steps at `review` status and drove it to `done`. No new stories were started.\n158\t\n159\t| Story | Phases Run | Outcome | Notes |\n160\t|-------|-----------|---------|-------|\n161\t| 5-1-flow-execution-sequential-steps | code-review, verification, proof-doc fix, AGENTS.md update | **Done** | 14/14 ACs verified. Commit `b983273`. |\n162\t\n163\t**Activities completed:**\n164\t1. Code review found 2 HIGH bugs and 2 MEDIUM issues — all fixed\n165\t2. Test-provable verification: 14/14 ACs passed, 3963 tests green, 99.2% stmt coverage on workflow-engine.ts\n166\t3. Proof document formatting fix (needed `**Tier:**` bold format)\n167\t4. `src/lib/AGENTS.md` updated to include `source-isolation.ts` and `workflow-engine.ts`\n168\t\n169\t---\n170\t\n171\t## 2. Issues Analysis\n172\t\n173\t### Bugs Found by Code Review (fixed)\n174\t\n175\t| Severity | Issue |\n176\t|----------|-------|\n177\t| HIGH | Per-story RATE_LIMIT/NETWORK/SDK_INIT errors did not halt the outer flow loop — only the inner work-items loop. Catastrophic failures would be silently swallowed. |\n178\t| HIGH | Dispatch failures did not record a TaskCheckpoint in workflow state, violating AC #13. Crash recovery would lose track of failed tasks. |\n179\t| MEDIUM | Coverage gaps — 8 new tests added. Coverage improved to 99.2% stmt / 87% branch. |\n180\t\n181\t### LOW Issues Deferred (not fixed)\n182\t\n183\t- Duplicate checkpoint creation logic in `dispatchTask` else branch\n184\t- `handleDispatchError` and `recordErrorInState` could be merged\n185\t- `warn()` calls for skipped tasks don't propagate to `EngineResult.errors`\n186\t- Branch coverage at 87% — remaining uncovered branches are defensive null checks on YAML parse results\n187\t- No integration test verifying actual YAML parsing (all YAML mocked)\n188\t\n189\t### Infrastructure Issues\n190\t\n191\t- **AGENTS.md was stale** — missing entries for `source-isolation.ts` and `workflow-engine.ts`. Fixed in this session.\n192\t- **Prior action item resolved:** Action item #1 from Session 1 (\"Complete code-review and verify for story 5-1\") is now done.\n193\t- **Prior action item resolved:** Action item #3 from Session 1 (\"Update AGENTS.md\") is now partially addressed (2 of 5 missing modules added).\n194\t\n195\t---\n196\t\n197\t## 3. Cost Analysis\n198\t\n199\t### Subagent Token Report (this session only)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01KaqZ6U2AkySNGGtJiznr8J","session_id":"a0646c12-93c6-41a0-