{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KWHCDZFqqhXTit81DQksBp","type":"tool_result","content":"4959\t\n4960\t---\n4961\t\n4962\t## 4. What Went Well\n4963\t\n4964\t1. **9 stories in ~5 sessions (Sessions 9-13).** Throughput of ~1.8 stories/session is strong for multi-phase execution.\n4965\t2. **Code review caught 8 HIGH bugs** including a path traversal, timer leak, assertion-less tests, and a rounding bug. Zero HIGH bugs escaped to verify.\n4966\t3. **All 9 stories passed verification** on first or second attempt. No story got stuck or required rollback.\n4967\t4. **Epics 12, 13, 14 closed.** Multi-framework driver support, output contracts, and TUI visualization all shipped.\n4968\t5. **Coverage held steady at 96.8%+** across 171 files, never dipping below the 80% floor.\n4969\t6. **Cost per story ($3.41) is under the ~$4 target.** Sprint is cost-efficient despite verification overhead.\n4970\t7. **Test count grew from ~4,478 to 4,614** (+136 tests) across 9 stories with zero regressions.\n4971\t8. **Small stories (15-1) completed cheaply** — ~15 lines prod code, 14 tests, clean run.\n4972\t\n4973\t---\n4974\t\n4975\t## 5. What Went Wrong\n4976\t\n4977\t1. **Verification is 45.5% of sprint cost.** The verify phase is the most expensive by far, and proof format mismatches are the primary driver of re-runs.\n4978\t2. **Proof format template is still broken.** 5 of 9 stories hit the same format mismatch (`### AC N:` vs `## AC N:`, `**Status:**` vs `**Verdict:**`). This has been flagged in multiple prior retros and remains unfixed.\n4979\t3. **`require-yield` lint error reported in 6 of 9 stories.** Pre-existing, never fixed. Pure noise adding to every verify cycle.\n4980\t4. **AGENTS.md staleness blocked 3 stories** at verify time. The doc-health check is useful but the docs themselves should be auto-generated.\n4981\t5. **`workflow-engine.test.ts` is a token sink.** Read 22+ times across the session block due to its size (800+ lines). Offset-based reads are necessary but expensive.\n4982\t6. **Spinner implementation is non-deterministic.** `Date.now()` for frame index means tests check \"any valid frame\" rather than a specific one. Fragile.\n4983\t7. **`dispatchTask()` public API is effectively dead code** — all internal callers use `dispatchTaskWithResult()`. Backward compat retained but adds surface area.\n4984\t\n4985\t---\n4986\t\n4987\t## 6. Lessons Learned\n4988\t\n4989\t### Patterns to Repeat\n4990\t- **4-phase pipeline (create-story, dev, code-review, verify)** continues to catch real bugs before merge. The 8 HIGH bugs this block validate the process.\n4991\t- **Small, well-scoped stories** (12-3 at ~100 lines prod, 15-1 at ~15 lines prod) are the cheapest and cleanest to execute.\n4992\t- **Test-provable ACs** eliminate the need for Docker/sandbox verification, keeping costs down.\n4993\t\n4994\t### Patterns to Avoid\n4995\t- **Skipping proof format template fixes** — this has been flagged in 3+ retros. Every unfixed session costs ~$8-12.\n4996\t- **Large test files** — `workflow-engine.test.ts` should be split. It's the #1 driver of redundant file reads.\n4997\t- **Dead code props** (`currentTask`, `dispatchTask()` legacy signature) — if not wired within 2 sprints, remove.\n4998\t\n4999\t---\n5000\t\n5001\t## 7. Action Items\n5002\t\n5003\t### Fix Now (before next session)\n5004\t\n5005\t| # | Action | Priority | Est. Savings |\n5006\t|---|--------|----------|-------------|\n5007\t| 86 | Fix proof format template in verifier — use `## AC N:` + `**Verdict:** PASS/FAIL` | HIGH | ~$8-12/sprint |\n5008\t| 87 | Fix `require-yield` lint error (pre-existing, 6+ sessions of noise) | HIGH | Noise reduction |\n5009\t| 88 | Auto-generate AGENTS.md at dev phase completion | MEDIUM | ~$3-5/sprint |\n5010\t\n5011\t### Fix Soon (next sprint)\n5012\t\n5013\t| # | Action | Priority | Est. Savings |\n5014\t|---|--------|----------|-------------|\n5015\t| 89 | Split `workflow-engine.test.ts` into focused files (800+ lines) | MEDIUM | ~$3-5/sprint in cache reads |\n5016\t| 90 | Split `ink-renderer.test.tsx` (881+ lines) into focused files | MEDIUM | Similar savings |\n5017\t| 91 | Combine vitest coverage + verbose into single command | LOW | ~$1-2/sprint |\n5018\t| 92 | Wire `update()` driverName from workflow engine to renderer | MEDIUM | Unblocks live driver display |\n5019\t\n5020\t### Backlog\n5021\t\n5022\t| # | Action | Priority | Notes |\n5023\t|---|--------|----------|-------|\n5024\t| 93 | Remove `currentTask` dead code prop or wire it | LOW | 3+ sessions as dead code |\n5025\t| 94 | Replace manual column spacing with `string-width` lib | LOW | Cosmetic alignment debt |\n5026\t| 95 | Inject clock/timer abstraction for spinner frame index | LOW | Enables deterministic tests |\n5027\t| 96 | Add combined crash-recovery + contract persistence test (13-3 AC 7 gap) | MEDIUM | Verification gap |\n5028\t| 97 | Add integration test for multi-driver workflow (14-3 AC 4 gap) | MEDIUM | Verification gap |\n5029\t| 98 | Fix pre-existing lint error in `src/templates/otel-config.ts` | LOW | Noise |\n5030\t\n5031\t### Cost Optimization Actions\n5032\t\n5033\t| Action | Est. Savings | Effort |\n5034\t|--------|-------------|--------|\n5035\t| Fix proof format template (#86) | $8-12/sprint | 30 min |\n5036\t| Auto-generate AGENTS.md (#88) | $3-5/sprint | 1 hour |\n5037\t| Split large test files (#89, #90) | $3-5/sprint | 2 hours |\n5038\t| Combine duplicate CLI commands (#91) | $1-2/sprint | 15 min |\n5039\t| **Total addressable waste** | **$15-24/sprint** | **~4 hours** |\n5040\t\n5041\t### Sprint Completion Status\n5042\t\n5043\t| Metric | Value |\n5044\t|--------|-------|\n5045\t| Stories done | 45/47 (95.7%) |\n5046\t| Epics complete | 14/15 |\n5047\t| Remaining | Epic 15: 15-2 (cost tracking per driver), 15-3 (driver capability matrix) |\n5048\t| Total sprint cost | $250.40 |\n5049\t| Total tests | 4,614 |\n5050\t| Coverage | 96.86% |\n5051\t| HIGH bugs caught by review | 8 (this block), 30+ (full sprint) |\n5052\t\n5053\t### Priority Recommendations for Next Session\n5054\t\n5055\t1. **Complete Epic 15** — 2 stories remaining: 15-2 (cost tracking per driver) and 15-3 (driver capability matrix/routing hints).\n5056\t2. **Fix proof format template (#86)** — highest frequency issue across sessions. Most cost-effective fix available.\n5057\t3. **Fix `require-yield` lint (#87)** — 6+ sessions of noise. 2-minute fix.\n5058\t4. **Split large test files (#89, #90)** — `workflow-engine.test.ts` and `ink-renderer.test.tsx` are the top token sinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01KaqZ6U2AkySNGGtJiznr8J","session_id":"a0646c12-93c6-41a0-9c7a-50683cae7716","uuid":"c3bffdaa-a6ef-442f-900c-c1b96ea53d8d","timestamp":"2026-04-03T13:11:25.776Z"}
